name: Subak Piak
address: H4V3+QX, Wongaya Gede, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: This place pleases your eyes with the beautiful view, especially when the sky is clear and you can see batukaru mountain as background. Come here when ricefield is green then you'll get even more prettier scenery
review 2: Very nice place. Peace and quiet.
review 3:
this is the natural version of jatiluwih

The people are very friendly and welcoming

The air is fresher than Jatiluwih because it's still full of rice fields here, there are no restaurants like in Jatiluwih, so it's recommended to bring your own food and then sit down in that area,I recommend this more than Bedugul whose entrance ticket does not match the quality of the facilities obtained

I hope the pepole is not contaminated for money oriented such as Jatiluwih & Bedugul
review 4: Nice and quiet to get some fresh air
review 5: Make sure you're arrive here in the morning to catch the best view of rice paddies.
